CRITICAL: Before doing anything in this repository, read AGENTS.md at
the repo root. It encodes deploy/ops/code conventions for a live
trading system. Violating those conventions has caused real
production incidents.

AGENTS.md is the single source of truth. The .cursor/rules/ folder
contains the always-apply rule that enforces this. This file (the
legacy .cursorrules format) exists for backward compatibility with
older Cursor versions.

Key invariants you MUST respect (full list in AGENTS.md):
- Docker service is `algo`, never `okx-straddle`
- Compose binary is `docker-compose` (hyphenated, V1), not `docker compose`
- Never use `--no-cache` on routine code-only deploys
- Tick rounding goes through `core.family.round_price_to_tick`
- `chase_buy` and `chase_sell` must keep `post_only=True`
- Session day-of-week is hardcoded in `config.SESSIONS`
